CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 19, 1941, reads: "Cupid Joins Prominent Pittsburgh Families At Delightful Home Ceremony - Prominent families were united when pretty and lovely Ethel Mae Cole, daughter of Mrs. Mae Cole Harris and Dr. William L. Cole, and James Harris, Jr., son of the James Harrises, Sr., were united in marriage at the residence of the bride's mother, Mrs. John Harris in Frankstown avenue. Ether Mae was a charming bride as these photos above will indicate...cutting the cake is Ethel Mae while James looks on...."
TitMainTitle: Groom James Harris Jr. and bride Ethel Mae Cole cutting three tiered wedding cake, in domestic interior with tree patterned wallpaper
